{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e3b6825e-e56d-4931-abad-e826b2672aa0","content":"There's no workflow file in this directory, so I'll give you the general guidance for the switch.\n\n## Changes needed for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n### 1. **NuGet.org setup**\n- Go to your package on [nuget.org](https://nuget.org) → **Manage** → **Publishing policies**\n- Add a **Trusted Publisher** entry with your GitHub repo owner, repo name, workflow filename, and optionally an environment name\n\n### 2. **Workflow changes**\n\nAdd `id-token: write` permission and replace the `dotnet nuget push` auth:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      contents: read\n      id-token: write          # ← required for OIDC\n    # Optional but recommended: pin to a GitHub environment\n    # environment: nuget-publish\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # ... build & pack steps ...\n\n      - name: Install .NET\n        uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: >\n          dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key differences from your current workflow\n\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` used in `--api-key` | No secret needed — remove `--api-key` entirely |\n| No special permissions | Add `permissions: id-token: write` |\n| — | `setup-dotnet@v4` handles token exchange automatically |\n\n### 3. **Remove the secret**\nOnce verified, delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo's **Settings → Secrets**.\n\nThe `setup-dotnet@v4` action automatically detects the OIDC environment and negotiates the token with NuGet. No API key is passed on the command line at all.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe2762ca-24b8-49b0-b716-286cf79cde9e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory seems empty. There's no workflow file to look at. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to OIDC trusted publishing. Let me give them guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":537},"id":"1a405128-4ce5-46a5-8f2d-e4c035a0d6ee","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:45:18.060Z","parentId":"6d8e5110-8916-40ef-acba-50c8570440a8"}
